Yes this is an issue that needs to be addressed by someone @ amazon. the problem is in the TransferManager class line number 834.
MultipleFileUploadImpl multipleFileUpload = new MultipleFileUploadImpl("Uploading etc", transferProgress, null, virtualDirectoryKeyPrefix, bucketName, uploads);

The third attribute is for ProgressListenerChain object that has been set to null. This value gets set in AbstractTransfer class instance attribute. So when you call the addProgressListener on MultipleFileUpload instance it internally calls this method in AbstractTransfer class

 public synchronized void addProgressListener(ProgressListener listener) {
        progressListenerChain.addProgressListener(listener);
    }

Since progressListenerChain is set to null, it throws NPE. But don't worry to get around this problem just surround the code in plain old try-catch block and your uploads will be fine. Hope this helps

